description.value:
Amsterdam's Rozentheater occupies an exclusive position as the only theatre in the Netherlands founded especially for young people. Based in an impressive building on the Rozengracht, they are all about contemporary, cutting-edge theatre.


Interdisciplinary location
The Rozentheater hosts amateur to (semi) professional productions and devotes stage time to intercultural and interdisciplinary pieces. So expect more than just theatre: you can also head to the Rozentheater for art, poetry, open mic sessions and evening/late-night events.

Rooms for hire
The main theatre seats 180 and the intimate small theatre holds 50 making it the ideal place for minor performances and readings. Both rooms as well as the foyer are available for hire.

description.value:
This former church, built in 1857, was renovated after falling into disrepair and has been reclaimed as a cultural centre in 2002.

The imposing Smits Organ had also seen better days, but it was restored to its former glory as well, returning to the de Duif in 2006.

Accessibility: The main entrance has three steps. Wheelchair users can access the venue through the entrance at Prinsengracht 754. The door has an accessible low doorbell. Through a long hallway, the church hall can be reached. There are glass doors with door closers. The church hall features a wide middle path with plenty of room for wheelchair users, even in the front of the hall. There are toilets located inside of the church, although they are not handicap friendly. The coffee corner is easily accessible.

description.value:
Monumentally Dutch
Designed by architect P.J.H. Cuypers and completed in 1876, Amsterdam's Rijksmuseum is the largest museum in the Netherlands. It houses a famous collection of Old Masters paintings including works by Rembrandt ('The Night Watch'), Vermeer and Frans Hals as well as delftware, sculpture, Asian art and prints.

Authentic sources from the past
The Rijksmuseum boasts an extensive cultural history collection which includes paintings, ship models, sculptures, archaeological artefacts, clothing, weapons, historical prints and photographs. The hundreds of thousands of items from the past collectively give a visual account of Dutch history within a global context.

Renovation
The Rijksmuseum is currently being renovated. Until the main building reopens in 2013, Golden Age masterpieces are on display in the Philips Wing on Museumplein. The rest of the museum's collection is showcased at the Rijksmuseum division in Amsterdam-Schiphol airport and at various domestic and foreign museums.

There is public transport in the vicinity of the location(within 500 m), Tram and bus stop in front of the building. Accessibility min. 80 and 90 cm. Difference in street/thresholdlevel max. 2 cm., automatic doors, halls accessible with lift, topfloor not accessible for wheelchairs. Special service: 4 wheelchair places inside halls, adapted lavatory present. Assistent dog, or guide dog allowed in.

time.value: Open daily from 9:00-18:00 hrs. Friday till 22:00hrs. Closed on January 1st.

description.value:
Opened in July 2007, The Amsterdam Public Library stands as a modern architectural gem on the Oosterdokseiland, just a five-minute walk east of Central Station.

European leader
The library is open 7 days a week and attracts in excess of 2.5 million visitors a year. It is not only the largest of Amsterdam's public libraries - at 28,000 m2, it's also the largest in Europe!

Dynamic design
The cutting-edge ecological design earned it the prize of 'Most Sustainable Public Building in Amsterdam'. The unique selection of seating allows you to take in amazing south-facing panoramic views.

More than a library
In addition to unique collections, the library boasts a theatre, a radio station, conference rooms, exhibition space, a music department, study pods, a readers cafÃ© and a restaurant with an outdoor terrace overlooking the city.

Join the club
As a registered library member, you can enjoy greater access to the library and its resources as well as reduced-price tickets and discounts at bookstores.

description.value: short

From 29 September 2012 until 25 April 2013, the Van Gogh Museum will be closed for renovations. A selection of highlights from the museum's world-famous collection will temporarily move to the Hermitage Amsterdam for a special 7-month exhibition: Vincent. The Van Gogh Museum in the Hermitage Amsterdam.

The Van Gogh Museum houses the world's largest collection of works by Vincent van Gogh as well as major works by other 19th-century artists.

Nowhere else in the world can you see so many of Van Gogh's paintings in one place. The museum allows you to follow the development of the artist's work through all its stages and compare it with paintings by other 19th-century painters in the collection.

The museum also runs a wide variety of temporary exhibitions focusing the history of 19th-century art.

Accessibility: the museum can be easily reached by public transport. There are two disabled parking spaces, one on the corner of Paulus Potterstraat and Van der Veldestraat, one on Paulus Potterstraat/Van Baerlestraat. The Van Gogh Museum is entirely accessible for wheelchair users. A separate entrance with lift is situated alongside the main Paulus Potterstraat entrance. All gallery halls are accessible by lift. There is a special emergency call service and disabled restrooms. There are also several wheelchairs available in the museum.

description.value: The National Maritime Museum reopened to the public in 2011 following considerable renovations. The museum is home to a diverse range of permanent exhibitions that explore numerous elements of maritime history. Permanent features of the museum include an extensive introduction to the Golden Age, when seafaring helped the Netherlands become a world power. Thereï¿½s a host of interactive displays, antique collections and even the chance to step aboard a replica of a 17th century Dutch East India Company ship, which is moored alongside the museum. You can also get to know the exhibits that bit more personally by taking a themed tour, led by one of the museumï¿½s enthusiasts.
Not accessible for wheelchair users or people with walking difficulties.

description.value:
The Bimhuis places Amsterdam firmly on the map as a leading European jazz city. Its roots date back to the early ï¿½70s, when local musos founded a new home for the local improv jazz scene in a former furniture salesroom. These days it shares a more bespoke performance space with the Muziekgebouw aan ï¿½t IJ, looking out over the River IJ. With 150 shows per year, itï¿½s not only the home of Dutch jazz, but also a port of call for the worldï¿½s best players.

Alongside the public concert hall, the Bimhuis also houses several studios where musicians can experiment with new material. The renowned VPRO/Boy Edgar Award for Dutch jazz music is presented at the Bimhuis annually.
Disabled visitors are advised to contact the Bimhuis in advance to discuss seating arrangements.

description.value:
A museum dedicated to the Amsterdam based writer, teacher, union member and social democratic politician Theo Thijssen (1879-1943). Thijssen is best known as the author of the novel Kees de Jongen.

The collection comprises manuscripts, first editions, pictures, drawings, images, recordings and personal effects of Thijssen. Besides the permanent exhibition, which illustrates the life and work of Thijssen, temporary exhibitions show aspects of the society he lived in and the different fields in which he was active: daily life in the Jordaan during the end of the 1800s, education during Thijssen's tenure as a teacher and socialism & the labour movement in the first half of the 20th century.

Besides being interesting for the many lovers of the literary work of Thijssen, the museum has something to offer for students, teachers, people who have an interest in social history and the history of Amsterdam, as well as for neighbourhood residents. The museum also has a small, specialised book store which not only sells works by and about Thijssen, but also (picture) books about the Jordaan area.

time.value: Open Thursday through Sunday from 12.00 until 17.00. Closed on holidays.

description.value:
A cinema steeped in history, Kriterion began life as a student association involved in hiding and saving many Jews from Nazi persecution in the Second World War. More than 65 years later, it has become a thriving cinema completely run by students.

Student action

In 1945 a resistance group led by students Wouter Zeytveld and Piet Meerburg created the cinema as a place of employment for students who would have otherwise had to discontinue their studies. On November 6, 1945, the cinema opened with a gala premiere for 200 guests.

Neighbourhood cinema

Kriterion is located across the road from the Psychology Faculty of the University of Amsterdam and still caters to the student crowd, art house cinema fans and loyal neighbours, creating a relaxed atmosphere for those wanting to see a film and share a drink in the bar afterwards.

Sneak peek

As well as showing the best in international art house cinema, the Kriterion also regularly hosts film and debate nights, Modern Classics and a very popular Sneak Preview night. It also facilitates several festivals and the increasingly popular Kriterion premiere parties are always highly anticipated.

Accessibility: there is a tram stop within 100 meters of the venue, a general handicapped parking zone can be found within 100 meters of the venue and it is also possible to drop off visitors in front of the cinema. Access: entrances have a minimum width of 80 to 90cm, the entrance can be fitted with a ramp, an elevator is present and the screening rooms can be reached by elevator. Wheel chair spaces are present in the screening rooms, a handicap friendly toilet is present in the venue, guide dogs or seeing eye dogs are allowed inside, the location is also completely smoke free.

Starting from humble beginnings as a temporary cinema in the cultural park of the Westergasfabriek, the Ketelhuis Cinema has grown into an important Amsterdam landmark for Dutch cinema and international art house and documentary film.

Movies & more

A team of volunteers are the driving force behind the Ketelhuis Cinema. Besides keeping an eye on the smooth projection of the films, the team also keeps the drinks flowing and food coming from behind the well-stocked bar.

Cinema for hire

The cinema boasts three screening rooms, the largest of these is capable of seating an ample 143 filmgoers. And if you're thinking of organising a gathering or throwing a party, the Ketelhuis Cinema is an ideal location: each of the screening rooms as well as the foyer area are available for hire.

Accessibility: Public transport within 500 metres of the location. Parking available within 100 metres. Access: entrances have a minimum width of 90cm. Two of the screening rooms are wheelchair accessible.

time.value: The box office is open from 14:00 until 22:00, on Wednesday and weekends from noon until 22:00. The Ketelhuis cinema is open until 01:00 during the week and until 03:00 during the weekend.

description.value:
With pop culture roots running back to the 1960s, Amsterdam's Paradiso is one of the city's leading music and clubbing venues.

Three Paradiso stages

Located close to the Leidseplein in the city centre, the converted former church building features a main concert hall with high ceilings and two balcony rings, a smaller, more intimate upstairs venue as well as a third venue in the basement.

Centre for pop culture

The venue attracts major domestic and international musicians and bands while recent years have seen the Paradiso embrace other disciplines including dance, theatre and film. Long-running club nights such as (Classic) Noodlanding! remain popular additions to the city's after-dark scene.
Parking for disabled visitors close by. Please call in advance to arrange disabled access. Upper floors and balcony accessible via lift.

description.value:
Please note that the Ajax Museum will unfortunately be closed until further notice due to refurbishment being carried out on the main entrance.

The museum portrays Ajax Football Club's history in photographs, historical documents, victory cups and trophies and personal artefacts of legendary Ajax players. The history of Ajax is rich and eventful, filled with emotion and heroism.

The club was founded nearly one hundred years ago and has since gained international fame. The museum in the Amsterdam Arena documents Ajax's rise; from the first games on grass on the outskirts of Amsterdam around 1900 to the legendary Europe Cup games that captivated a worldwide audience right up the to present day and into the future.

Visitors to the museum can marvel at the exhibits of the museum's permanent collection, and it is also possible to take a guided tour of the stadium.
Accessible. Lift available to enter museum. There is a special guided tour for wheelchair users, using the larger lifts. Special restroom avaiable.

description.value:
Since 1995 the Theatercompagnie resides in a former church adjacent to the Nieuwmarkt.

The building was designed in 1793 by city architect Abraham van der Hart for the Lutherian Congregation. Until 1984 the building was in use as a church, followed by a period where it had many functions. In 1995 De Theatercompagnie, founded in 1988 by director Theu Boermans, was given a ground lease on the building. Many classic plays have been performed on its stage including Twelfth Night, A Midsummer Night's Dream, and Hamlet, and some of the actors who blossomed here have moved on to television and film roles. Delft-based architecture firm Mecanoo was responsible for the transformation of the church into a theatre. The interior of the Compagnietheater is a beautiful combination of both historic and modern elements.

description.value:
Inspiring, innovating and international

The Muziekgebouw aan 't IJ opened its doors in the spring of 2005. The spectacular building justifiably calls itself 'Amsterdam's Concert Hall of the 21st Century'. The music performed in the Muziekgebouw always aims to be both inspirational and innovative, with an exciting, contemporary programme.

Music and more...

But world-class music is not the only reason to visit the Muziekgebouw. Throughout the year, the venue hosts exhibitions showcasing work by internationally acclaimed visual artists. And why not call in on the Star Ferry? The Muziekgebouw cafe and restaurant allows visitors the chance to enjoy a wide range of food & drinks and offers a fabulous view of the IJ.

Get a 25% discount with your I amsterdam Card!

Thursday nights are where it's at for lovers of contemporary music, thanks to the Muziekgebouw's Thursday Night Series (Donderdagavondserie). The programme features highlights of the varied musical programme at the self-proclaimed 'Concert Hall of the 21st Century'. This season, a total of 30 concerts will bring you nothing but the very best in contemporary sounds.
Disabled access, audio induction loop for visitors with a hearing aid.

description.value:
Located opposite the Melkweg in the bustling heart of the city, Amsterdam's Cinecenter is the place to be for the latest independent and art house films.

Location, location, location

The Cinecenter cinema combines a very convenient location with a stylish, futuristic interior with four intimate screening rooms. The building was originally designed by architect Gerard de Klerk and was restyled in 1998 as a lounge bar.

Latin lounging

Cinecenter specialises in art house films from the French and Spanish speaking regions. The modern bar is the perfect place to relax with a glass of wine before and after the fim and is also available to hire for private functions.

Accessibility: fair. Visitors can use the handicapped parking spaces on the Marnixstraat 400. There is also a possibility to drop off visitors in front of the cinema. Parking in the immediate neighbourhood is difficult, most parking spaces are equipped with a meter. The sidewalk lacks a ramp. The entrance has a small threshold and there cinema has a wide door with a door closer. Usability: poor. The box office is high up and has a glass window without an intercom. Three of the screening rooms and the toilets can only be reached using a flight of stairs. There is no handicap friendly toilet. Screening room 4 is accessible for wheel chair users.

time.value: Reservations can be made by phone, starting half an hour before the start of the first screening. Since the box office takes precedence over answering the phone, it may prove difficult to reach the Cinecenter during peak hours. Currently, there is no way to reserve tickets online.

description.value: Visit the hiding place where Anne Frank wrote her diary during World War II. For more than two years, Anne Frank lived secretly with the other people in hiding in the back part of her father's office building at Prinsengracht #263. The Secret Annex has been preserved in its original state. The front part of the building - the offices where the 'helpers' worked - has been restored to the style and ambiance of the war years. Quotations from the diary, photographs, films and original objects belonging to the people in hiding and those who helped them all serve to illustrate the events which occurred at this location. Anne's orignal diary is on display in the museum along with some of her other notebooks. The museum's interactive 'Free2choose' exhibition explores the present-day boundaries of freedom.

The Anne Frank House is not easily accessible for the physically disabled. People who are physically disabled should notify the Anne Frank House in advance of a visit so that it can be determined if an appropriate guided tour can be arranged.

time.value: Open daily from 9:00 to 19:00. From 15 March through 14 September from 9:00 to 21:00. From 15 March through 14 September on Saturdays from 9:00 to 10:00. The library contains a large number of interesting collections, such as the Library of the Book Trade, the Bibliotheca Rosenthaliana, old Amsterdam editions and cartography, church collections on Dutch protestantism and a collection on the university's history.
The exposition hall is wheelchair-accessible and the location has two parking spaces for the disabled at the rear entrance.

description.value: The Beurs van Berlage, designed by Berlage, was build in 1903 to be used as a commodity exchange, a function it held far into the eighties. Since then concerts are held in both halls. In the main hall fairs and events are commonly held. The other halls are used for lectures and congresses. The Dutch Philharmonic Orchestra and the Dutch Chamber Orchestra hold their rehearsals here. Besides, the venue is often visited by national and international ensembles.

Het is ook mogelijk om voor te rijden, er is een goede trottoiroprit bij de ingang. Toegankelijkheid - goed. Er is geen niveauverschil bij de entree. In de hal is het niveauverschil overbrugd door een hefplateau. De deuren bij de ingang staan altijd open. Bruikbaarheid - redelijk. De balies en de garderobe zijn aan de hoge kant. De foyer is goed toegankelijk. Aangepaste toiletten en een wandtelefoon aanwezig. In de Yakultzaal zijn in het gangpad een aantal eersterangs opstelplaatsen voor rolstoelgebruikers. In de AMVEST Zaal zijn in het gangpad op rij 12 en 13 opstelplaatsen. Deze zaal ligt op een hoger niveau, maar er is een hellingbaan. Bij de ingang ligt een kleine drempel. Beide zalen zijn voorzien van een infrarood-installatie voor slechthorenden. Voor toegang tot de Grote Zaal wordt u geholpen door de suppoosten.

description.value:
Amsterdam's Spaarndammerplantsoen is home to three imposing social housing blocks designed by Michel de Klerk. The expressionist apartment block popularly known as Het Schip (The Ship) is one of the best examples of the early 20th-century Amsterdam School architectural movement.

Museum Het Schip is located in the former post office, which was also designed by De Klerk. The impressive building is a feast for the eye but also provides plenty of food for thought by addressing questions including how and why Amsterdam turned into a social housing mecca and the cultural-historical value of the Amsterdam School.

The museum also provides access to a restored working class house, the exhibition on the Amsterdam School's sources of inspiration and an opportunity to see Michel de Klerk's world-famous tower.

description.value:
Wie een kaartje met de Amsterdamse musea bekijkt, ziet daarop geen enkel museum in Amsterdam Noord aangegeven, terwijl dit stadsdeel een geschiedenis heeft die teruggaat tot in de 12 eeuw. Alleen daarom al is een museum in en van Noord onontkoombaar. Amsterdam-Noord heeft niet alleen een interessante geschiedenis, maar is ook bezig zich op te maken tot een bedrijfseconomisch en cultureel stadsdeel in de voorhoede. Aan de langgerekte noordelijke oever van het IJ verrijzen het komend decennium moderne industrieÃ«n, culturele instellingen, uitgaansgelegenheden en futuristische woonwijken.

Het Gemeente Badhuis is in 1919 gebouwd in het kader van de bouw van het Vogeldorp als tijdelijke huisvesting in het kader van de volkswoningbouw. Het was bedoeld voor ongeveer vijftien jaar, maar die termijn is wel zodanig overschreden, dat het dorp inclusief het Badhuis inmiddels een monumentenstatus heeft gekregen. De woningen zijn opgeknapt en gemoderniseerd, maar het Badhuis verloederde. Totdat Stadsherstel Amsterdam N.V. eigenaar werd en tot restauratie overging. De Stichting Museum Amsterdam Noord was blij in staat te worden gesteld het te huren en in gebruik te nemen als stedelijk geschiedenis- en kunstcentrum.

description.value:
Odeon is a club situated in the heart of the Amsterdam Canal Ring. Built in 1662, the building housed a brewery and a warehouse before it was rebuilt as the first proper indoor concert venue in the Netherlands in 1837.

Modern club in classical architecture

The building that houses Odeon started life as the Nuerenburg House, designed by architect Philips Vingboons. In 1837, the house was transformed into a concert hall and its was name is changed to Odeon. After a fire gutted the building in 1990, renovations partly restored the building to its former glory before a subsequent renovation in 2003 completed the job, also restoring the classical elements.

Dance and events

Since reopening in 2005, Odeon has regained its standing in the cultural life of Amsterdam. Besides renting out space for private functions, meetings and weddings, Odeon is the home of several popular electronic music parties, plays a prominent part in the Amsterdam Dance Event that takes place every autumn and also hosts the premier Halloween party in Amsterdam.

description.value:
Located in the bustling heart of Amsterdam, the Melkweg (Milky Way) is one of the city's leading entertainment venues with two halls, a cinema, a theatre and a cafe - and a varied live programme.

Music at the Melkweg
The Melkweg boasts three outstanding halls to support their varied live music programme. The intimate Oude Zaal plays host to up-and-coming bands while The Max regularly welcomes established names. The latest adddition is the Rabozaal: a modern, multifunctional hall connected to the Stadsschouwburg and ideal for seated concerts.

The Milky Way
Housed in an old dairy factory, the Melkweg played a major role in 1960s-counterculture Amsterdam. Alongside live music, the location is also home to theatre productions, films, exhibitions and regular dance events.
Good accessibility. Public transport nearby, disabled parking spaces, lift available.

description.value:
Inspiring, innovating and international
The Muziekgebouw aan 't IJ opened its doors in the spring of 2005. The spectacular building justifiably calls itself 'Amsterdam's Concert Hall of the 21st Century'. The music performed in the Muziekgebouw always aims to be both inspirational and innovative, with an exciting, contemporary programme.

Music and more...
But world-class music is not the only reason to visit the Muziekgebouw. Throughout the year, the venue hosts exhibitions showcasing work by internationally acclaimed visual artists. And why not call in on the Star Ferry? The Muziekgebouw cafÃ© and restaurant allows visitors the chance to enjoy a wide range of food & drinks and offers a fabulous view of the IJ.

Get a 25% discount with your I amsterdam Card!
Thursday nights are where it's at for lovers of contemporary music, thanks to the Muziekgebouw's Thursday Night Series (Donderdagavondserie). The programme features highlights of the varied musical programme at the self-proclaimed 'Concert Hall of the 21st Century'. This season, a total of 30 concerts will bring you nothing but the very best in contemporary sounds.
Disabled access, audio induction loop for visitors with a hearing aid.

description.value:
Restored to former glory Built in 1935, the PathÃ© City Theater cinema is not only steeped in tradition but also one of the city's architectural highlights. The original building was designed by Jan Wils, the architect who also conceived Amsterdam's Olympic Stadium. The building was closed for renovation back in 2007 but once again throws open its doors to the film-hungry public on 2 December 2010.

Entertainment for the modern age Located amidst the hustle and bustle of Amsterdam's Leidseplein, the building has been drawing the crowds for premieres since the 1930s. Thanks to the recently completed facelift, it is now set to become an entertainment complex for the modern age. The PathÃ© City is certainly not run-of-the-mill and the programming is set to be decidedly arthouse. In addition to the seven screens of the cinema itself, the building houses a welcoming lounge, the Little Buddha sushi bar and even a casino. The perfect plan for a rainy day!

description.value: Amstelpark is a magical place for young and old. The park features a huge variety of plants and creative gardening layouts, due to the fact that it was originally built for the Floriade in 1972. This â€œgarden showâ€ event takes place every 10 years, and professional gardeners from around the world create spectacular displays just for the Floriade. After the event was over, the Amstelpark was turned into a public park, but they preserved a number of the original displays and layouts. Amstelpark has a petting zoo just for children, but itâ€™s not uncommon to see chickens and rabbits throughout the entire park. There is also a very large playground and a small train that loops around the park from April to October.

description.value: Formerly a squat, and a film academy before that, OT301 is a multi-media and alternative culture centre. These days it is home to concerts, parties, film nights, arts workshops and music studios, a non-profit print shop and vegan restaurant De Peper. In 2007, it received the Amsterdamprijs voor de Kunsten (Amsterdam Prize for the Arts) by Mayor Job Cohen.

description.value:
The latest addition to the city's thriving jazz scene, the North Sea Jazz Club recently opened for business at Amsterdam's Westergasfabriek.

Jazz hotspot

Head to the club on Friday and Saturday evenings for an intimate meal before live acts take to the stage. DJs take to the decks later in the evening, keeping the dance floors grooving until the small hours.

Progressive acts

Thursday evenings at the North Sea Jazz Club are reserved for progressive live acts with a distinctly danceable vibe. Future plans include introducing a special family brunch programme on Sundays, in collaboration with the Conservatorium van Amsterdam.

Bar & restaurant

Open daily, the club bar & restaurant also features a small stage welcoming the best up-and-coming acts. On club evenings, it becomes a late-night bar offering drinks and bar food.

description.value:
Located in the heart of the city on the Nes, Theater De Engelenbak (The Angel's Seat) was founded in 1975 to accommodate and promote amateur theatre performers.

Subsidised by the City of Amsterdam, De Engelenbak cooperates with performers of all forms of art who show potential, innovation, originality and passion towards their craft. All forms of art are welcome at the theatre: from drama, dance and mime to youth theatre, music, opera, comedy and cabaret. The intimate venue seats 110 people and there is a small bar/waiting room for before and after-performance drinks.

time.value: Ticket sales and reservations at the ticket office at the Brakke Grond, Nes 45, Mon - Sat 13:00 till start programme (or 18:00 when there is no programme sceduled.)

The grounds are home to numerous businesses, bars, restaurants, a cinema and a theatre and the renovated industrial buildings and spacious park regularly host events ranging from major club nights to art exhibitions and culinary happenings.
Good accessibility, the Westergasfabriek features plenty of concrete paths and open spaces.

description.value: The Oude Kerk, oldest church in Amsterdam, is now a centre of cultural activities in the heart of the old town centre. The beautiful light through the high windows, the medieval church furnishing, gravestones (such as Saskia van Uylenburgh's, Rembrandts first wife) and the magnificent painted wooden vaults, create a unique atmosphere and give away something of the buildings' unique history. The Oude Kerk has been built in different phases and ages and has a total area of 4000 m2. There are two organs: a transept organ (1658) and the well-known Vater-MÃ¼ller organ (1724/1738), nowadays both used for concerts. Besides cultural events, exhibitions, concerts, dinner parties, receptions, presentations and meetings, the monument is open to general visitors.

Possible to drive up the entrance. No difference street/entrance level. Large doors. The churchfloor consists of gravestones and has several steps, which make access fairly difficult. There are special facilities for the hearing impaired (ringlead) and there's a special restroom.

description.value:
ARCAM Amsterdam Centre for Architecture was set up as a foundation in 1986 and concentrates its activities in Amsterdam and the surrounding area.
ARCAM aims to reach the largest possible public in order to broaden architecture's appeal and zeros in on topical issues and developments in Amsterdam, so that the discussion about the future is constantly fuelled.
ARCAM also has a function as co-ordination centre and works together with a large number of institutes in order to support and co-ordinate existing programmes and to initiate new activities.
Accessible with help.

description.value:
The Tolhuistuin ('Toll House Garden') is Amsterdam's new cultural hotspot. The Stichting Cultuur aan het IJ ('Foundation for Culture on the IJ') is transforming the site into a cultural refuge for all types of art, boasting a large cafÃ©/restaurant, a sun terrace on the River IJ, three theatre and concert halls, exhibition rooms, a hip-hop school and a children's art hall. The Tolhuistuin can be found one hundred metres away from the Buiksloterweg ferry on the former Shell site on the bank of the IJ.

This summer, there will be a dazzling preview of what to expect of the Tolhuistuin crew. Together with their partners they offer an appetizer of the kind of place they want to be(come): adventurous and surprising programmes, an open space in a tight city, an easy-going atmosphere and a well-selected variation of 'something for everyone'. The golden rule: you never really know what you're going to get, but it's always a thrill. See below for full programme.

description.value: Bovendien huisvest het Pakhuis de kantoren van Cultuurfabriek, Waag Society, het Amsterdams Fonds voor de &nbsp:Kunst en Salto Omroep Amsterdam. Naast een grote zaal met een capaciteit van 300 tot 600 personen, zijn er nog drie kleine zalen en een exporuimte in het gebouw.

Architectural feat
The original warehouse was built in 1934 and should have been demolished when the Eastern Docklands area underwent a major renovation. A bridge was meant to be built where the warehouse stands, but thanks to a petition the warehouse was declared a national monument. The final solution was a unique one &ndash: to build the bridge right through the middle of the building!

Multifunctional space
Pakhuis De Zwijger houses a café:, multiple halls and meeting rooms, radio and television studios, and multimedia workshops. Located on the Piet Heinkade above the Jan Schaeffer bridge, the warehouse also holds the offices of several cultural organisations. In addition to an auditorium that can seat up to 600 people, the building also features three smaller meeting rooms and an exhibition space.

Alle ademen de rijke sfeer van de Gouden Eeuw. d?Vijff Vlieghen is toonaangevend vanwege zijn Nieuw Nederlandse Keuken. De chef-kok heeft hiervoor de culinaire historie van ons land als uitgangspunt genomen. In de Nieuw Nederlandse Keuken wordt uitsluitend gewerkt met verse Nederlandse producten, die op eigentijdse wijze worden verwerkt.

Restaurant d'Vijff Vlieghen occupies five adjoining 17th century houses. The restaurant has nine interconnected dining rooms, each with its own distinct style. All of them recreate the atmosphere of the Golden Age. d'Vijff Vlieghen now is leading because of its New Dutch Cuisine. The chef has based his style on Holland's culinary traditions whilst adapting them to the tastes of today. In the New Dutch Cuisine is only worked with daily fresh Dutch ingredients.

Bij As geen vast menu, maar steeds wisselende gerechten die bereid worden met mooie verse producten. Bijvoorbeeld scharrelvlees, biologische groenten, bier van lokale brouwers en zelfgebakken brood. Restaurant As is in an old church right near the business district Zuid-As. Upstairs is an exhibition space devoted to the revolutionary Platform 21, and downstairs you can enjoy delicious authentic dishes on long tables. As has no fixed menu, but rather an ever-changing array of dishes prepared with fresh ingredients such as free-range meat, organic veggies, locally brewed beer and homemade bread. You can dine in the marvellous homey interior or outside on the patio surrounded by the garden.

It?s a popular hangout in summer, with one of the area?s largest outdoor terraces.

Vanuit je kuipstoeltje eet je verse kreeft, kalfstong, houtduif en zeetong, als het maar in het seizoen is. Bordewijk is eigenlijk een klassiek kwaliteitsrestaurant in een modern jasje.

With its light, cool interior and with its many windows, Bordewijk on the Noordermarkt (North Market) is a bit like being in a goldfish bowl but it is a place where one can dine excellently. Settled in bucket-seated chairs one can enjoy fresh lobster, tongue of veal, wood pigeon or sole when in sason. Bordewijk is actually a classic first-class restaurant in a modern style.

description.value: Op het pittoreske Bickerseiland zit eetcafÃ© 't Blaauwhooft, met een groot terras. Van buiten ziet het er redelijk nieuw uit, van binnen zit het vol met historische details als glas-in-lood, zeegezichten en ronde bollampen. Avond na avond zit het hier vol met vrolijke drinkers en eters uit de buurt. Op de kaart staan traditionele eetcafÃ©gerechten als satÃ©, mosselen en kaasfondue en er worden legio activiteiten georganiseerd: van het kijken naar voetbalwedstrijden en het Eurovisiesongfestival op groot scherm tot live muziek op zaterdagavonden.

Situated on the picturesque Bickerseiland with a big terrace is bar food cafÃ© 't Blaauwhooft. On the outside it looks pretty new but inside it is full of historic details like stained glass, paintings of sea views and spherical glass lamps. Every evening it?s packed with a happy crowd of drinkers and diners from the neighbourhood. There are typical traditional bar food dishes on the menu such as satÃ©, mussels and cheese fondue. They organise endless activities: everything from football matches and the Eurovision song contest on a big screen to live music on Saturday evenings.

Naast buurtbewoners komen daar ook makelaars, reclamemensen en advocaten van in de buurt liggende kantoren op af. ?s Zomers is er een groot terras in de zon, 's winters zit je lekker knus aan de houten tafeltjes met waxinelichtjes. De zogenaamde ?vrimibo? (vrijdagmiddagborrel) in BÃ©dier is inmiddels legendarisch.

CafÃ© BÃ©dier was the first really pleasant local cafÃ© in Amsterdam Zuid (South). It is a 'brown cafÃ©' with a bright bunch of customers and a first class bistro menu. As well as locals, it gets filled with estate agents, media people and lawyers from the neighbouring offices. In the summer, there is a big terrace in the sun and in winter it is cosy inside with wooden tables and little candles. The so-called ?vrimibo? (Friday afternoon drink with colleagues) in BÃ©dier has become something of a legend.

Voor de deur is een terras gemaakt met wit Italiaans designmeubilair. Ook het (kleine) betaalbare menu is Italiaans met klassiekers als insalata caprese, tonijncarpaccio en pollo al vino. Na het eten kun je aan de professioneel geschudde cocktails en mingelen met de incrowd van Oost.

Near the Hotel Arena and the Oosterpark (East Park) is bar/restaurant Caffe Milo. The retro-interior of this delightful corner building is in many shades of brown with 60s lamps and curved forms. In front, there is a terrace with white Italian design furniture. The small (and affordable) menu is also Italian with classics such as insalata caprese, tuna carpaccio and pollo al vino. After dining, there is the pleasure of professionally- shaken cocktails and mingling with the incrowd of East Amsterdam.

description.value: Aan de westkant van de stad zit Caffe Oslo, een bar/restaurant met een Scandinavisch retro-interieur met veel grote lampen, bruintinten en hertengeweien aan de muur. Het retro-gevoel wordt hier ver doorgevoerd: uit de boxen klinkt veel jaren '80 muziek en het publiek is niet veel ouder dan dertig. In het restaurantgedeelte eet je diverse pasta's maar ook serieuze hoofdgerechten als gemarineerde hertenbiefstukjes en aardappel-truffelpannenkoekjes. Let op: Oslo is immens populair, dus reserveren noodzakelijk.

Caffe Oslo is in the west of the city- a bar/restaurant with a Scandinavian retro-interior with lots of huge lamps, brown tones and deer antlers on the wall. The retro-atmosphere is exploited to the full with music from the 80s playing: though the customers are not yet in their thirties. The restaurant serves up a variety of pastas but also serious main courses such as marinated venison steaks and potato truffle pancakes. Warning: Oslo is immensely popular so it?s best to book ahead of time.

description.value: Authentiek Peruaans eten op de Amsterdamse grachten? Dat kan bij Casa Peru op de hoek van de Leidse- en Prinsengracht. Het restaurant heeft een groot terras aan het water en serveert typisch Peruaanse gerechten als ceviche de pescado (rauwe vis), estofado de carne con papas (in rode wijn gestoofd rundvlees) en aguadito (maaltijdsoep van zeevruchten en vis). Om het af te toppen kun je je tegoed doen aan warme chocoladetaart en Peruaans citroengebak.

Authentic Peruvian food on an Amsterdam canal? Well, yes ? at Casa Peru on the corner of the Leidsegracht and the Prinsengracht. The restaurant has a huge terrace on the water and serves typical Peruvian dishes such as ceviche de pescado (raw fish), estofado de carne con papas (beef stewed in red wine) and aguadito (filling seafood soup). And to finish with, there are desserts such as warm chocolate pie and Peruvian lemon cake.

Casa di David on the Singel is your typical Italian restaurant with bruschetta, Caprese salad and pizzas but also pasta with truffles. The Italian service is fast and noisy and the restaurant is always packed. Note: It's not the best Italian in town but it's a charming spot to eat well.

description.value: Aan het water van de Westlandgracht, vlakbij het Hoofddorpplein, ligt een modern glazen gebouw met daarin het chique restaurant Cedars. Bij Cedars kun je eerst een aperitief drinken in de zogenaamde loungeroom, om vervolgens authentiek Libanees te eten. Denk aan een tafel vol met mezze (kleine gerechtjes), maar ook hoofdgerechten als lamsrack en gemarineerde zeebaars van de houtskoolgrill. Op een van de twee terrassen aan het water zit je ook nog eens erg idyllisch.

At the waterside of the Westlandgracht (Westland Canal), not far from the Hoofddorpplein, is a modern glass building which houses the chic restaurant Cedars. At Cedars one can start with an aperitif in the so-called lounge room and afterwards enjoy authentic Lebanese cooking on either of the two terraces. Think of a table full of mezze (small dishes) but also of main dishes such as rack of lamb and marinated sea bass from the charcoal grill.

Ook de omgeving is prettig: interieurstylist Eric Kuster (Jimmy Woo) maakte chique ruimtes met fluwelen stoelen, geborduurde zijden gordijnen en orchideeÃ«n.

At the Chang-I restaurant round the corner from The Royal Concertgebouw (Concert Hall), one can enjoy modern Chinese cuisine in glamorous surroundings. The Chang brothers serve finger-licking good Eastern food. Drool over coquilles with black beans, lobster with garlic and ginger and Irish tenderloin in sweet and sour sauce. Lovely decor as well: interior stylist Eric Kuster (Jimmy Woo) creates a chic space with velvet chairs, embroidered silk curtains and orchids.

Local ingredients are treated to creative preparations by chef Onno Kokmeijer, with a sprinkling of luxury ingredients like caviar and black truffle in all the right places. The panoramic view on the 23rd floor is a breath-taking addition to the meal.

Zo proefden The Rolling Stones, George Clooney en Joe Cocker allemaal van de goddelijke dorade in zoutkorst, vitello tonnato en penne arrabiata. De sfeer is ook al zo goed: je kunt elkaar soms niet verstaan door het Italiaanse gekakel van het bedienend en keukenpersoneel, waardoor je je echt even in Napels waant.

World stars have known about this place for years: the best Italian food in the city is served up at the family restaurant d?Antica in the Reguliersdwarsstraat. The Rolling Stones, George Clooney and Joe Cocker have all delighted in the heavenly fish in a salty crust, vitello tonnato and penne arrabiata. The Italian atmosphere is so genuine ? sometimes there is such overwhelming chatter and cackle amongst the waiters that you can imagine that you really are in Naples.

De grote ruimte is strak en zakelijk ingericht met roodoranje leren banken, witte pilaren en veel glas. Dit is een echte brasserie: de plateaus fruits de mer zijn niet aan te slepen, net als de biefstukken met friet, halve kreeften en pannetjes mosselen. Het publiek varieert van pakkenmannen tot fraai uitgedoste dames.

A former Renault garage right near the Amstel station has been turned into CafÃ©-restaurant Dauphine ? which is also the name of a Renault car from the 50s. This vast space is now cool and business-like with burnt orange leather couches, white pillars and a monumental amount of glass. This is a real brasserie: one can?t get enough of the dishes of fruits de mer, steak with fries, half lobsters and pans of mussels. Customers range from boys in business suits to women beautifully dolled up.

In the up-and-coming Zeeburg district is the charming cafÃ© De Cantine. In the former canteen of the juvenile prison eat moderately priced international dishes like lamb curry, steak or cheese fondue. There is an artistic feel to the place and on a regular basis activities are organised: pop quizzes, films, exhibitions and live performances (every Sunday).

In the middle of the Jordaan is cafÃ© De Tuin. The decor of this high-ceilinged building is charmingly untidy, with an oakwood bar with a drinks cupboard, wooden panelling on the walls and framed antique posters. At the front, students, intellectuals and beer drinkers noisily discuss the world at length but at the back, one can have a quiet moment with a glass of special Belgian beer (Tongerlo, LaChouffe, Floreffe) on tap.

's Zomers kun je hier heerlijk in de tuin eten.

For unusual Asiatic dishes in combination with some beautiful people-watching, go to Dynasty in the Reguliersdwarsstraat. In this colourful and rather old-fashioned interior with walls hung with Walasse Ting paintings, one can enjoy dishes such as lobster and goose liver Asian style as well as Peking duck and turbot with lemon grass. In summer time one can dine in the garden.

Behalve voor een drankje kun je hier ook terecht voor betaalbare broodjes, appeltaart en mediterrane gerechten.

Festina Lente on the Looiersgracht is actually more like a cosy living room than a cafÃ©. The decor is a mishmash of things and they have lots of board games available. There are wood tables, a few comfy lounge chairs and a sweet resident cat. It is the owners? philosophy that we all take time to enjoy life. Festina Lente means ?Make haste slowly? in Latin, and the young crowd here take this to heart. As well as drinks you can also get reasonably priced soup, rolls, apple-pie and Mediterranean dishes.

This is one restaurant that stands for delicious food, but that's not all. Freud employs a 70 member-strong staff that have all suffered from psychiatric issues. Beethoven Street in Amsterdam is a nice shopping center with national stature. It's located on the edge of the new business center of Amsterdam. In this street you'll find the Steakhouse Gauchos. Herengracht is a modern chic place with a good terrace facing the water. Inside it is comfortable and lavish with soft couches and plenty of places to sit. On the menu are classics such as vitello tonnato, carpaccio and sashimi. For many business people in the city centre, this is the perfect place for networking. On the walls is the work of artist Peter Donkersloot. There is a permanent exhibition of his figurative paintings: from a giant portrait of Marilyn Monroe to a comical piglet.

description.value: Hemelse Modder is de naam van een hemels chocoladedessert, maar ook van een restaurant met fraai terras in het oude centrum van de stad. Het restaurant heeft een eenvoudig interieur met houten tafels en stoelen en een houten vloer. De keuken staat al een aantal decennia hoog aangeschreven en komt met gerechten als Zuid-Franse vissoep en artisjok gevuld met cantharellen. En uiteraard voor toe: de onovertroffen hemelse modder.

Hemelse Modder is the name of a heavenly chocolate dessert but also of a restaurant with a beautiful terrace in the old centre of the city. The restaurant is simply decorated inside with wooden tables and chairs and a wooden floor. The cooking here has been highly regarded for decades. They produce dishes such as fish soup from Southern France and artichokes stuffed with chanterelle mushrooms. The menu is frequently to feature seasonal produce. And, of course you can try the exquisite &quot:Heavenly Mud&quot: dessert to finish your meal.

De inrichting is eenvoudig, de kok maakt veel lawaai en de bediening is uitbundig: precies zoals het hoort bij een Italiaan. Het eten speelt hier de hoofdrol. Verwacht gerechten als kwarteltjes met citroenrisotto, verse pasta?s en gegrilde zeebaars of lamskoteletten.

Italian restaurant Hostaria in the Jordaan is small and snug. Every evening fans of real Italian cooking come here to eat. The decor is simple, the chef is noisy and the waiters are exuberant- exactly as one would expect in Italy itself. Eating takes centre stage here. Expect dishes such as quail with lemon risotto, fresh pasta and grilled sea bass or lambs cutlets.

description.value: Italiaan Incanto heeft een uniek uitzicht: het sfeervolle restaurant ligt op de eerste en tweede verdieping van een pand aan de Amstel en kijkt uit op de historische Munttoren en de Bloemenmarkt. Maar ook het eten is erg de moeite waard. De Venetiaanse chef kookt mooie gerechten als gnocchi met kreeft en wilde eendenborst met mosterdfruit. Daarbij heb je keus uit meer dan 150 verschillende Italiaanse wijnen. Op de derde etage is een speciale rokerslounge met comfortabele stoelen.

The Italian Incanto has a unique view: this charming restaurant is on the first and second floors of a building facing the Amstel River and looks out over the historic Munt Tower and the Bloemenmarkt (Flower Market). The chef from Venice cooks beautiful food like gnocchi with lobster and wild duck breasts with mustard fruit. Add to the setting and menu a choice of more than 150 different Italian wines and it makes Incanto a must for Italian lovers. On the third floor there is a special smokers' lounge with comfortable chairs.

Denk aan een soep van geroosterde paprika?s en op de huid gebakken heek met ansjovis en citroen.

A French pearl is hidden on the Ringdijk in the Watergraafsmeer: restaurant La Vallade. It has a country-style interior with French antiques and it has a big terrace full of flowers and plants. One eats what is on the daily menu: a five-course dinner for a reasonable price. These are pure Mediterranean dishes without fuss. Think of a soup of grilled peppers, baked hake with anchovies and lemon.

A popular terrace in the summer around cocktail hour, you can eat delicious tapas, as well as salads and somewhat more serious dishes like leg of lamb or sea bass. At Le Hollandais on the Amsteldijk one feels like a god in France. This charming restaurant with excellent and friendly service is renowned for its authentic French dishes. Chef and owner Adriaan is constantly striving for the new and creative: homemade sausages, organic vegetables, offal, sustainably- harvested fish and game. This is serious eating so take your time.

At a busy crossroads in Amsterdam-Zuid (South) is cafÃ©-restaurant Fidelio. Inside is very old-fashioned and the menu is simple, but nevertheless every evening the place is full. The place draws in the old locals, students and everything in between. Its popularity is partly because Fidelio is the only cafÃ© in the area, but also due to the warm hospitality. The large corner terrace is the ideal spot for checking out the chic passersby on the Beethovenstraat.

description.value:
Locatie
Tussen het grote aanbod oude Aziatische horeca valt restaurant Looks meteen op. De eerste indruk van de twee oude monumentale panden is die van een traditioneel restaurant. Maar als je de deur opent betreed je een warme, moderne, internationale, urban gelegenheid. Bij de entree begroet het keukenteam je vriendelijk. Door de open keuken kan de gast direct zien dat er gewerkt wordt met verse producten.
Het gebouw bestaat uit allerlei niveauverschillen verbonden met trappetjes. De ruimtes hebben een eigen karakter en doorkijk. Door veel spiegels en het gebruik van verlicht glas ontstaat er een eenheid.

Menu
Looks heeft kleine kaart die iedere 6 weken wisselt. Oesters, Entrecote en Kreeft staan vast op de kaart. De wisselende kaart is verrassend en prikkelend, Looks kookt met alle seizoenen mee. Het restaurant wil je als gast graag verrassen en bereiden bekende ingredië:nten vaak net even anders.

In the old city centre, bang between all the Asian haunts, is the modern bar/restaurant Looks. The restaurant is spread out over different levels and has hidden niches, lots of mirrors and a big open kitchen. From here emerge impeccable seasonal dishes made with local produce. There is always a choice of three dishes. A menu standard is the dikbilkoe (double-muscle cow) entrecÃ´te from Weesp and the Dutch oysters.

This cosy little restaurant ? which has modern furnishings but also things like candles and rose petals to generate the right atmosphere ? has been a favourite of many an Amsterdam resident for years now. description.value: Wat doe je als je als chef-kok geen zin meer hebt in een overvol, groot restaurant waar je avond na avond gerechten van de menukaart staat te koken? Je begint een huiskamerrestaurant zoals Marius in de Barentszstraat. In een rommelige, knusse zaak, kookt chef-kok Kees Elfring uit een klein keukentje dagelijks een (prijzig) culinair marktmenu. De sfeer is net als het eten geweldig, juist omdat je zo dicht op elkaar zit en het er zo informeel aan toe gaat.

What does a chef do when he no longer feels like running a big, crowded restaurant where evening in and evening out he must slave in the kitchen to produce dishes on the menu? What he does is start a small living-room restaurant like Marius in the Barentszstraat. In a charming, cosy establishment in a small kitchen, brilliant chef Kees Elfring creates a daily culinary (but quite expensive) market menu. Both the atmosphere and the food are fabulous: the informality and being tucked in closely with other diners adds to the pleasure.

For Indian cuisine in modern surroundings go to restaurant Mayur and the adjacent lounge bar Mayur Delight. The Sharma family have been serving Northern Indian specialities here following traditional recipes for years. There is meat that has been marinated for 24 hours before being cooked in the tandoor (wood stove). The only trace of Western influence is the extensive wine and champagne list and the decor of velvet and wood.

Bar/restaurant Nassau is on the corner of the Tweede Nassaustraat and the De Wittenkade in the west of the city. Its interior is fresh, breezy and light (windows all round) and has a bit of a retro feel without being too smooth and designy. At mealtimes, the old locals can be seen enjoying the Wiener schnitzel or wolf fish elbow-to-elbow with the young creative crowd. There is a big patio of wooden decking with directors chairs, vines and lavender plants to complete the Cannes atmosphere in Amsterdam?s West district.

Nooch is a hip Asian restaurant in De 9 Straatjes (The 9 Streets). Minimalist decor with a long bar eat Japanese dishes (sushi, yakitori, beef teriyaki) as well as Chinese (Peking Duck Pancakes) and Thai dishes (Thai lobster, Thai beef salad) ? and according to the owner they all bring ?good fortune?.

Hier geen gouden draken of lampionnen aan de muur, maar een strak interieur met basalt-blokjes muur en comfortabele bruine leren designstoelen. Beneden kun je aan de cocktails, boven heeft het restaurant iets huiskamerachtigs. Hier zitten reclamemensen, studenten en toeristen zij aan zij aan de traditionele Chinese gerechten, zoals pekingeend, makreel met zwarte bonensaus en gestoomde oesters. In tegenstelling tot bij de traditionele Chinees, kun je er hier wÃ©l een goed glas wijn bij bestellen.

On the corner of the Vijzelstraat and the Herengracht is a modern Chinese restaurant, P.King. None of your golden dragons or lanterns on the walls here but in their place, a cool decor with walls of basalt blocks and comfortable brown leather designer chairs. Go downstairs for cocktails and upstairs for the restaurant with its living room feel where its clientele of media people, students and tourists come to eat traditional Chinese dishes such as Peking duck, mackerel with black bean sauce and steamed oysters. Unlike other traditional Chinese restaurants, a decent glass of wine can be ordered

Restaurant Oriental 128 on the Amstelveenseweg proves that French and Chinese cuisine go well together. The dishes served up in this rather chic place (crystal, silver plate cutlery) are a combination of the finest of Chinese cooking substantiated by the best of French ingredients. Consider sea bass with a poached egg, stir-fried quail with fried duck liver and roast Peking Duck.

In the busy Overtoom sits the relaxed restaurant Peper & Zout, simply decorated with wooden flooring, white barstools, patterned tablecloths on the wooden tables and photos of old Hollywood stars on the wall. The menu has international dishes such as sashimi, carpaccio and grilled tuna: there is also a rotating weekly three-course menu.

On the grounds of the Science Park Amsterdam, between the institutes of learning, is cafÃ©-restaurant Polder. With its pleasant atmosphere, serving all day long, order a scrambled egg breakfast, a sandwich for lunch or from the copious dinner menu ? much of which is made from organic ingredients. When it's cold outside, curl up in one of the armchairs by the wood-burning stove. When the weather is fine, eat at the picnic tables on the outdoor terrace.

In a picturesque alley not far from the Nes is Kapitein Zeppos. This cheerful cafÃ© is in a nineteenth century warehouse and has a bit of a Mediterranean atmosphere because of the colourful walls, the conservatory full of greenery and the terrace. They play French chansons but they also have regular live performances as well. The rather international menu has dishes prepared from seasonal ingredients.

Vanuit de kleine keuken worden namelijk lekkere Italiaanse klassiekers bereid. Carpaccio, vongole, vitello tonnato, tiramisu: ze staan allemaal op het menu, voor redelijke prijzen. Je zit wat krap en de bediening is soms chaotisch, maar dat maakt het wel lekker authentiek Italiaans.

Ponte Arcari is on the Herengracht, near the Utrechtsestraat. This small Italian restaurant is, not surprisingly, nearly always full. In the tiny kitchen really delicious classic Italian food is prepared: carpaccio, vongole, vitello tonnato, tiramisu all for a reasonable price. True, the service is slightly chaotic, with customers elbow-to-elbow but that's what gives the authentic Italian atmosphere.

Eating is an art at Proef Amsterdam on the Westergasterrein (West Gasworks Grounds). The food has been 'designed' by Marije Vogelzang who serves up unusual culinary experiments. In this beautiful, industrial space with its long wooden tables with stools, one tastes continually changing (organic) concepts - a real experience each time.

Quattro Gatti in the Negen Straatjes (the 9 Streets) is a typical small Italian restaurant. In a cantine-like atmosphere one eats pure authentic Italian dishes such as veal with truffels, charcoal-broiled sausages and pasta with fresh lobster. Everything is homemade: from the bread to the pasta and desserts. The restaurant is much loved and it is small ? it has seating for only 22 ? so make sure you call ahead of time to book a table.

The menu has mainly fish: from a club sandwich with lobster and steamed turbot to grilled sea bass with octopus risotto. But for the red-meat lovers dine on succulent lamb chops. Restaurant Seven Seas in Grand Hotel AmrÃ¢th serves up French /international kitchen and a fine wine selection but what is so remarkable is the location. It is actually in the monumental Scheepvaarthuis (Shipping Building) which dates from 1914- one of the first structures built in the Amsterdam School style. The marble floor, wooden panelling, stained glass ornament and original detailing blow you away while dining.

The menu has classics such as Thom Kha Kai and beef in red curry with a good glass of wine from the wine business opposite, Chabrol.

Italian restaurant Toscanini has been a hot spot in the Jordaan already for a couple of decades. The big open space is full every evening with couples, groups of friends, colleagues, in-laws and families. The food is always perfectly prepared with the best ingredients. Some of the best dishes are fish (sometimes raw) and the heavenly pastas and tasty organic pork dishes. This place is so pleasant to dine in that one can look forward to a long, late, happy evening.

In this charming corner building with white wall tiles and wooden floor, authentic Italian dishes are served without fuss. There is a menu but the dishes are written up every day on a board- in Italian. From melanzane parmigiana and rigatone alla siciliana to scaloppini and panna cotta.

description.value: Op het Oosterdokseiland, vlakbij het Muziekgebouw aan het IJ vind je de bekende restaurantketen Vapiano. In een casual design interieur met veel natuursteen en hout, een kruidentuin en een echte olijfboom kunnen honderden mensen aanschuiven voor een steenovenpizza, huisgemaakte pasta of salade. De snelle koks maken alles vers voor je neus en als je speciale wensen hebt, kun je die ook gewoon te kennen geven.

On the Oosterdokseiland, not far from the Muziekgebouw aan het IJ (Music Building on the IJ) is the famous chain restaurant Vapiano. In a casual design interior with los of natural stone and wood, a herb garden and a real olive tree, hundreds of people can enjoy pizza from a brick kiln or homemade pasta or salad. The cooks are fast and make everything in front of you. If you have special wishes then all you have to do is ask.

description.value: Restaurant Vasso behoort inmiddels tot de klassiekers van de stad. Het mooie restaurantje vlakbij het Spui, trekt fijnproevers en - door de locatie - ook veel toeristen. Hier zwaaien Italianen de scepter, tot aan de bediening aan toe. Aan de houten tafeltjes eet je perfecte Italiaanse klassiekers ? van penne gorgonzola tot filete di manzo en pannacotta - voor pittige prijzen. Ook is er, ter afsluiting, een indrukwekkende lijst met grappa?s.

Restaurant Vasso has become one of the classics of Amsterdam. This striking restaurant, located just a stone?s throw from the Spui, attracts all the foodies and, because of the prime location, several tourists as well. The Italians rule the roost here, including the table service. At the wooden tables, one can savour classic Italian dishes: penne gorgonzola and filete di manzo and pannacotta, at a price. Even more, they have an extensive list of grappa on offer.

description.value: Vinkeles is een warm, sfeervol en luxe restaurant, gevestigd in The Dylan Hotel Amsterdam. Het team deelt met u de passie en voorliefde voor het moois wat de eigentijdse Franse keuken te bieden heeft. Met veel aandacht voor de kracht, kleur en smaak van het product. Het restaurant is bekroond met een michelin-ster.

One part French, one part Dutch, and a smattering of molecular gastronomy make up the menu at Michelin-starred Restaurant Vinkeles. Situated in boutique The Dylan Hotel on the picturesque Keizersgracht, the location is secondary to the regionally inspired menu showcasing local ingredients. Texel lamb is a must try.

description.value: Schuin tegenover congrescentrum Rai zit restaurant Vis aan de Schelde. Het restaurant kent vele fans, een van de redenen dat je hier zelden spontaan kunt binnenlopen voor een tafeltje. In het overwegend blauwe interieur kan de visliefhebber z?n hart ophalen. Van sashimi en kreeft tot gebakken heilbot en gepocheerde roggevleugel. Voor vishaters zijn er altijd een of twee vleesgerechten te bestellen.

Diagonally opposite the Rai congress centre is restaurant Vis aan de Schelde. The restaurant has many fans, which is one of the reasons one can?t just walk in and hope to get a table. In the mainly blue colour of the decor, lovers of fish dishes can eat to their heart?s content. There is sashimi and lobster and baked halibut and poached skate. For the non-fish eaters there are always a couple of meat dishes on the menu.

Het interieur van Winkel is uitermate eenvoudig en licht en de bediening altijd voorkomend.

The Winkel homemade apple cake is renowned across Amsterdam. Winkel is also an ideal spot to enjoy a convivial meal and drink in the evening too. One can enjoy the views over the Westerstraat and Noordermarkt from the terrace. On Friday nights the apple cake bakers work overtime to cater to the organic Saturday market visitors queuing at the door.

Sip a homemade limoncello on the restaurant?s terrace during the summer. Reservations are recommended, or take your pizza to go.

Yamazato, in the Amsterdam?s Okura Hotel, is arguably one of the best Japanese restaurants in Europe. This traditional restaurant earned a Michelin star for its sublime Japanese dishes and serene Zen Bhuddhist interior. Pristine sushi is melt-on-the-tongue fresh, but it?s the kaseiki menu that really shows off the chefs? skills.

Op de kaart uitdagende smaakcombinaties als een salade met artisjok, mozzarella en tomatendressing, lasagne van gamba?s en avocado en entrecÃ´te met rivierkreeftensaus. Allemaal voor schappelijke prijzen.

On the Ceintuurbaan is cafÃ©-restaurant Zabayon, where everything is fresh, homemade and reasonably priced. In a beautiful simple interior in shades of brown enjoy Mediterranean dishes with daring combinations such as a salad with artichokes, mozzarella and tomato dressing, a lasagne of gambas and avocado, and entrecÃ´te with crayfish sauce.

description.value: Japans eten in een zen-omgeving kan bij Japans delicatessenhuis Zen in de Pijp. Het knusse, kleine restaurantje heeft slechts een paar tafeltjes, maar die zijn nooit onbezet. Dat komt waarschijnlijk door de lekkere, authentiek Japanse gerechten die op elegant serviesgoed gepresenteerd worden. Denk aan superverse sushi en sashimi, maar bijvoorbeeld ook zeewiersalade, yakitori en zalmteriyaki. Ideaal voor een lunch of early supper, want helaas sluit Zen al om acht uur.

This neat, small restaurant only has a couple of tables but they are never empty. The delicious and authentic Japanese dishes presented on elegant plates coupled with a relaxed environment gives that feeling of zen. Dine on super fresh sushi and sashimi, seaweed salad, yakitori and salmon teriyaki. An ideal place for a lunch or early supper as Zen closes at eight o?clock, how very Zen.

Goede wijn drinken op het terras met hangplekken, wat smakelijke hapjes erbij, aparte gerechten eten in het restaurant en terug naar het bargedeelte voor een afzakkertje. Het interieur is strak, maar ook tijdloos en sfeervol door het kleine oppervlak en het rumoer. Iedere laatste zondagavond van de maand is er live muziek.

Stout! in de Haarlemmerstraat is a place where you can easily spend an entire evening. Drink great wine on the terrace, eat snacks, great dinners in the restaurant and then back to the bar. The interior is timeless and cosu. Every last Sunday of the month there is live music.

description.value:
Culinair dineren
Door middel van verse, seizoensgebonden producten worden er gerechten gecreë:erd die de smaakpapillen prikkelen, vandaar ook de naam. De gastvrijheid van de familie Zakai zorgt er samen met de filosofie van Chef kok Dennis van Tintelen voor dat iedereen een avond culinair kan genieten van de Frans-Mediterraans georië:nteerde keuken. ":Waar de kunst van het koken, het verfijnen van de eenvoud is":.

Restaurant VandeMarkt verwelkomt een ieder die zich graag culinair in de watten laat leggen, of het nou aan de Chefs Table is of gezellig met zijn tweeë:n.

Puur genieten
Wijn en spijs combineren tot in perfectie is waar VandeMarkt voor staat. Gasten kunnen genieten van bijzondere wijnarrangementen, zorgvuldig samengesteld door de sommeliers met wijnen uit eigen wijnkelder, Wine-Wijn.

Wine-Wijn
Wine-Wijn is de grootste wijnkelder van Nederland in een restaurant. Gasten vinden hier een unieke collectie van wel 500 verschillende wijnen, likeuren en champagnes. Rondleidingen, proeverijen of een wijncursus, bij Wine-Wijn kunnen wijnliefhebbers hun geluk niet op.

Groepsarrangementen
Private dining Restaurant VandeMarkt is daarnaast geschikt voor zowel particulieren als zakelijke gasten. Je kunt in het restaurant terecht met een groep van minimaal 25 personen en maximaal 64 personen in diner opstelling. Groepen kunnen hier in een unieke setting vergaderen of privé: lunchen en dineren. Graag bespreekt het restaurant met jou de mogelijkheden.

Meaning &lsquo:from the market&rsquo:, the name VandeMarkt says it all. The restaurant focuses on fresh, seasonal products to create sophisticated yet simple dishes that let the ingredients shine. Come experience the warm hospitality of the Zakai family and the French/Mediterranean-inspired creations by chef Dennis van Tintelen.

Restaurant VandeMarkt caters to those who enjoy the finer things in life, whether you want to experience a grand tasting menu at the chef&rsquo:s table or have an intimate dinner for two. VandeMarkt is also known for its skill in picking the perfect wine to match each dish. Speak to their sommelier for expert advice or order a special wine arrangement to complement your meal.

VandeMarkt is also the perfect location for business dinners or special occasions. The private dining area can accommodate anywhere from 25 to 64 guests. Call or email the restaurant to discuss the possibilities.

The large space is filled with comfortable vintage armchairs, sofas, tables and retro chairs, tiered pendant lamps and even a cabinet of board games, which explains why this place calls itself a bar, restaurant and living space.

The menu features everything from oysters and pasta to veal and smoked mackerel filet. You can literally spend the entire day here! Order coffee on the waterside terrace, enjoy a cocktail at the bar, get a salad for lunch or sit down for a full dinner. They also have free Wi-Fi.

Come early to grab a seat outside on the small canal-side terrace.

description.value:
Probeer bij een bezoek aan Scossa zeker het antipasti buffet, de specialiteit van het huis. Of kies voor het verleidelijke, 3 gangen menu, een persoonlijke selectie van executive chef Michel Westerman, met de beste seizoen&rsquo:s ingredië:nten. Scossa&rsquo:s menu wordt gecompleteerd door een uitgebreide selectie van internationale wijnen uit gerenommeerde wijngaarden die perfect bij de gerechten passen.

Alles in Scossa gebeurt rond de bruisende open keuken, een echte eyecatcher in het restaurant, die een onderhoudende dialoog tussen de chef en zijn gasten creë:ert. Voel de energie van de keuken in combinatie met het moderne design, terwijl je geniet van het uitzicht over historisch Amsterdam. Er is een delicaat evenwicht in het restaurant tussen ontspannen en bruisend, dat velen nastreven maar weinigen voor elkaar krijgen met zoveel allure als Scossa.

description.value: Bierfabriek

The Bierfabriek is a jonkie (youngster) among the tasting rooms, but this brewery in Amsterdam?s centre is already packed with visitors clamouring for their red ale, dark porter, or pilsner. Private tap tables are a draw for groups: a meter shows how much you drink. Don?t miss the barbecued beer-marinated chicken - it?s already a classic.

description.value:
De culinaire steak experts gaan graag een gesprek met je aan over de fijne kneepjes van goede steaks en de bereiding ervan. Steakliefhebbers kunnen hun hart ophalen met de signature 1.6 kilo T-bone, die met zeezout gegrild wordt tot de ultieme sappigheid: een geweldig gerecht om met vrienden te delen.

Alle gerechten zijn klassiekers en geï:nspireerd door de keukens van de eersteklas steakhouses in New York. Het menu wordt gecompleteerd door een uitgebreide selectie internationale wijnen uit gerenommeerde wijngaarden die perfect bij de gerechten op het menu passen.

Het restaurant heeft een warme Amerikaanse sfeer met een fantastisch uitzicht over het bruisende deel van Amsterdam tussen het Vondelpark en het Leidseplein. Alle zintuigen worden geprikkeld door de bruisende ambiance, de open show keuken en onweerstaanbare gerechten. Geniet na het diner van een geweldige cognac en sigaar in de privé: Midtown Cigar Lounge.

These days, however, it&rsquo:s more of a cultural hangout. As well as being a picturesque spot to wine or dine, the location is home to unique performances, jazz concerts and &rsquo:50s-inspired parties, such as those by Razzin&rsquo:. This monumental building can also be hired for weddings, meetings and other private events.

CafÃ© BÃ©dier was the first really pleasant local cafÃ© in Amsterdam Zuid (South). It is a 'brown cafÃ©' with a bright bunch of customers and a first class bistro menu. As well as locals, it gets filled with estate agents, media people and lawyers from the neighbouring offices. In the summer, there is a big terrace in the sun and in winter it is cosy inside with wooden tables and little candles. The so-called ?vrimibo? (Friday afternoon drink with colleagues) in BÃ©dier has become something of a legend.

Start with a drink on the terrace, pop inside for the Mediterranean dishes, then make your way to the bar for more drinks. The decor here is pretty retro and the DJs make for a lively atmosphere. Near the Hotel Arena and the Oosterpark (East Park) is bar/restaurant Caffe Milo. The retro-interior of this delightful corner building is in many shades of brown with 60s lamps and curved forms. In front, there is a terrace with white Italian design furniture. The small (and affordable) menu is also Italian with classics such as insalata caprese, tuna carpaccio and pollo al vino. After dining, there is the pleasure of professionally- shaken cocktails and mingling with the incrowd of East Amsterdam.

description.value: Aan de westkant van de stad zit Caffe Oslo, een bar/restaurant met een Scandinavisch retro-interieur met veel grote lampen, bruintinten en hertengeweien aan de muur. Het retro-gevoel wordt hier ver doorgevoerd: uit de boxen klinkt veel jaren '80 muziek en het publiek is niet veel ouder dan dertig. In het restaurantgedeelte eet je diverse pasta's maar ook serieuze hoofdgerechten als gemarineerde hertenbiefstukjes en aardappel-truffelpannenkoekjes. Let op: Oslo is immens populair, dus reserveren noodzakelijk.

Caffe Oslo is in the west of the city- a bar/restaurant with a Scandinavian retro-interior with lots of huge lamps, brown tones and deer antlers on the wall. The retro-atmosphere is exploited to the full with music from the 80s playing: though the customers are not yet in their thirties. The restaurant serves up a variety of pastas but also serious main courses such as marinated venison steaks and potato truffle pancakes. Warning: Oslo is immensely popular so it?s best to book ahead of time.

This evocative cafÃ© is in an authentic building with high, ornamented ceilings and serves delicious affordable food such as typical cafÃ© classics like cheese fondue, mussels and chicken satÃ©?all with a touch of daring in the preparation. In the middle of the Jordaan is cafÃ© De Tuin. The decor of this high-ceilinged building is charmingly untidy, with an oakwood bar with a drinks cupboard, wooden panelling on the walls and framed antique posters. At the front, students, intellectuals and beer drinkers noisily discuss the world at length but at the back, one can have a quiet moment with a glass of special Belgian beer (Tongerlo, LaChouffe, Floreffe) on tap.

Behalve voor een drankje kun je hier ook terecht voor betaalbare broodjes, appeltaart en mediterrane gerechten.

Festina Lente on the Looiersgracht is actually more like a cosy living room than a cafÃ©. The decor is a mishmash of things and they have lots of board games available. There are wood tables, a few comfy lounge chairs and a sweet resident cat. It is the owners? philosophy that we all take time to enjoy life. Festina Lente means ?Make haste slowly? in Latin, and the young crowd here take this to heart. As well as drinks you can also get reasonably priced soup, rolls, apple-pie and Mediterranean dishes.

They welcome you with open arms at Dulac in the Haarlemmerstraat. Nothing is too much for the staff and the clientele of students, couples and tourists enjoy every moment of it. The cafÃ© is vast, theatrical and fairy-tale like with plenty of little alcoves, walls painted with trumpets, saxophones, hanging antlers and French posters from 1900 and, standing centrally, a large pool table. What is more, you can eat splendidly here and in the summer dine in the garden.

On the Zeeburgerstraat, with a view of a windmill, is the cafÃ© Langendijk. A popular terrace in the summer around cocktail hour, you can eat delicious tapas, as well as salads and somewhat more serious dishes like leg of lamb or sea bass. At a busy crossroads in Amsterdam-Zuid (South) is cafÃ©-restaurant Fidelio. Inside is very old-fashioned and the menu is simple, but nevertheless every evening the place is full. The place draws in the old locals, students and everything in between. Its popularity is partly because Fidelio is the only cafÃ© in the area, but also due to the warm hospitality. The large corner terrace is the ideal spot for checking out the chic passersby on the Beethovenstraat.

The food is reasonably priced, very good and quite simple with, for example, aubergine lasagne, lamb chops and pappardelle with chicken and green pesto.

On the grounds of the Science Park Amsterdam, between the institutes of learning, is cafÃ©-restaurant Polder. With its pleasant atmosphere, serving all day long, order a scrambled egg breakfast, a sandwich for lunch or from the copious dinner menu ? much of which is made from organic ingredients. When it's cold outside, curl up in one of the armchairs by the wood-burning stove. When the weather is fine, eat at the picnic tables on the outdoor terrace.

Tot ver buiten de stadsgrenzen is de Van Dobben croquet een begrip. De beroemde Van Dobben-croquetten zitten op met roomboter besmeerde kadetjes en zijn zeldzaam lekker. Het is er echt Amsterdams wat de klok slaat.

De eetsalon is een instituut op het gebied van de Nederlandse broodjes cultuur dat niet mag ontbreken na een dagje Amsterdam.

This typical Amsterdam deluxe lunchroom is the meeting place of artists, soccer players and many other locals. Its Van Dobben croquette is famed far beyond the city limits. A great place to eat traditional Dutch food. You can get them freshly served by typical Amsterdam waiters, it doesn't get more Amsterdam than this.  Great pea soup with ham, corquettes and other such delicacies. Well priced and cheery atmosphere. This is their second shop and close to the famous Albert Cuyp Market.

Bagels &: Beans
In de Ferdinand Bolstraat 70 opende Bagels &: Beans voor het eerst haar deuren, begin 1996. Middenin het hartje van de Pijp, tegenover de Albert Cuypmarkt. Sustainable products
Bagels &: Beans is serious about sustainability, which is why nearly every ingredient used in their products is organic or fair trade. Their coffee is selected with as much care as the food, and comes from the Janson Estate in Panama.

Bagels &: Beans Ferdinand Bolstraat
Located opposite the Albert Cuypmarkt at Ferdinand Bolstraat 70, the original Bagels &: Beans first opened its door in 1996. It still draws a mixt of locals, students and tourists throughout the day. Open every day from 8:00, Bagels &: Beans is the ideal spot for breakfast, coffee or lunch.

description.value: Banketbakkerij, tearoom en ijssalon Lanskroon vind je in het centrum van Amsterdam. Naast de heerlijke koekjes, wafels, taarten en chocolade verkoopt Lanskroon elk jaar vanaf 1 april ambachtelijk bereid room- en sorbetijs.

Lanskroon turns out gorgeous sweet and savoury pastries in the centre of Amsterdam. Their traditional Dutch favourites are made with love and care, and it?s one of the few places in town where you can still buy homemade stroopwafels. Starting each year in April they serve homemade ice cream as well ? perfect alone, but even better with a slice of cake.

description.value: Op zomerse dagen zie je eerst de rij voordat je Monte Pelmo, een kleine ijssalon in hartje Jordaan, zelf ontwaart. Monte Pelmo is een ambachtelijk ijsbedrijf sinds 1957 en is meerdere malen uitgeroepen tot de lekkerste ijssalon van het centrum van Amsterdam. Probeer eens een bolletje strawberry cheesecake of ?witte kus? (witte chocola met hazelnoten) en je begrijpt vast waarom.

On sunny days, you?ll see the queue before you see Monte Pelmo itself ? a tiny ice cream shop hidden in the Jordaan. Founded in 1957, it?s often been voted the best ice cream in the city centre. After you try a scoop of their strawberry cheesecake or tiramsu flavours, you?ll probably agree.

description.value: De aanleg van de noord-zuid lijn, biedt Amsterdam-Noord een uitgelezen kans op het realiseren van een park. Het biedt de mogelijkheid om het Volewijkspark en het Florapark tot een nieuw park samen te voegen; het Noorderpark. Met een nieuw circuit (van ongeveer 2 kilometer), voor fiets- en voetgangers worden de verschillende deelgebieden met elkaar verbonden. Het Noordhollandsch Kanaal komt daarbij in het hart van het park te liggen. Het park wordt nieuw leven ingeblazen en weer een levendig groen hart voor Amsterdam-Noord. Met een evenemententerrein, kinderspeellaatsen, visplekjes, hondenuitlaatgebieden, horeca, mooie entrees en een zonneweide.

description.value: De Rode Hoed is een voormalige schuilkerk, het is de grootste en oudste van Nederland die bewaard is gebleven.

Bereikbaarheid - redelijk~ Voor de deur zijn 3 parkeerplaatsen, het zijn laad- en losplaatsen die tevens als invalidenparkeerplaats kunnen worden gebruikt. Het is mogelijk om voor te rijden. Er is geen niveauverschil in het trottoir en de rijweg.~ Toegankelijkheid - redelijk~ De entreedeur en de tochtdeur zijn breed, en hebben geen drempel. Bij de entree zit een hoge bel.~ Bruikbaarheid - redelijk~ Er is een lage kassabalie. Op de begane grond ligt de grote zaal, op de 1e verdieping de vergaderzaal en op de tweede verdieping de kleine zaal. De verdiepingen zijn alleen per trap bereikbaar. In de grote zaal zijn diverse opstelplaatsen voor rolstoelgebruikers aanwezig. De foyer in de hal is goed toegankelijk. Er is een aangepast toilet en een publiekstelefoon. De telefoon is hoog op de wand geplaatst. Er is geen ringleiding.

description.value:
Deze sfeervolle bibliotheek is gehuisvest in de zijbeuk van de monumentale Ritakerk aan het Hagedoornplein. De collectie bestaat uit 25.000 boeken, 1.800 luisterboeken, cd-roms en games en bijna honderd binnen- en buitenlandse kranten en tijdschriften. Naast een aantrekkelijke leestafel zijn er diverse rustige studie- en werkplekken. Ook voor de jeugd is er veel te beleven, zo is er een aantrekkelijke hoek met boekjes voor baby’s, peuters en kleuters. 
In de bibliotheek worden wisselende exposities van kunstenaars uit Noord gehouden, ook zijn er jaarlijks fototentoonstellingen over het oude Noord. Regelmatig vinden er activiteiten plaats voor zowel kinderen als volwassenen. Een overzicht staat in de agenda op deze website.
OBA-leden kunnen dagelijks een half uur gratis gebruik maken van de internet pc’s in de bibliotheek. Niet-leden betalen € 1,00 per 30 minuten.
